        Building Certificates in Brisbane: When Sellers Need One and What It Covers
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;color:rgba(240,236,228,0.6);line-height:1.8;max-width:54ch;">
        A building certificate confirms that an approved structure complies with its approval. It is not a clearance for everything on your property, and confusing the two can create problems at contract or settlement.
      </p>
